==English==

===Interjection===
'''[[heads]] [[up]]'''
#{{idiom}} An informal [[warning]], [[caution]], or call for [[attention]]; pay attention.
#:'''''Heads up'''!  I'm about to let go.''
#:'''''Heads up'''!  The boss is coming.''

===Noun===
'''heads-up''', '''heads up'''
#{{idiom}} A warning or call to pay attention; an advisory notice.
#:''Send everyone a '''heads-up''' about the inspection tomorrow.''
 

